// WebSocketHandler
// Manages all WebSocket connections for the server and routes broadcast messages
// to all clients or to clients subscribed to a specific item or channel.

Connections are stored in a Set. Each connection carries a subscriptions Set in its
data payload, holding item IDs and "channel:<name>" strings. Dead connections (those
that error on send) are removed lazily after each broadcast pass.

Subscriptions are item-scoped (by diagram/document/spreadsheet/snippet ID) or
channel-scoped (by a named channel string stored as "channel:<name>").

FUNCTION handleConnection(ws)                                           EXPORT
  Initialize the connection's subscriptions as an empty Set and add it to the
  connections pool.

---

FUNCTION handleDisconnection(ws)                                        EXPORT
  Remove the connection from the pool.

---

FUNCTION handleMessage(ws, message)                                     EXPORT
  Parse the incoming JSON message.
  IF type is "subscribe": add the item ID or "channel:<channel>" to this connection's
  subscriptions.
  IF type is "unsubscribe": remove it.
  Ignore malformed messages.

---

FUNCTION broadcast(message)                                             EXPORT
  Send the message to every connected client. Collect any that error, then remove
  them from the pool to prevent memory leaks.

---

FUNCTION broadcastToDiagram(id, message)                                EXPORT
  Send the message only to clients whose subscriptions include this diagram ID.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION broadcastToDocument(id, message)                               EXPORT
  Send the message only to clients whose subscriptions include this document ID.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION broadcastToSpreadsheet(id, message)                            EXPORT
  Send the message only to clients whose subscriptions include this spreadsheet ID.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION broadcastToSnippet(id, message)                                EXPORT
  Send the message only to clients whose subscriptions include this snippet ID.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION broadcastNotification(notificationData)                        EXPORT
  Wrap the notification data in a "notification" message and broadcast to all clients.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION broadcastStatus(status, message, lastActivity)                 EXPORT
  Wrap the status, optional message, and lastActivity timestamp (defaulting to now)
  in a "status_changed" message and broadcast to all clients.
  Remove dead connections after the pass.

---

FUNCTION getConnectionCount() -> number                                 EXPORT
  Return the current number of tracked connections.
